---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Resume Roast">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 text-gray-300">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mb-8">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Welcome to Resume Roast. By accessing or using our website, services, or creating an account, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms") and our <a href="/privacy" class="text-orange-500 hover:text-orange-400 underline">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, you may not access the Service.
        </p>
        <p>
          These Terms apply to all visitors, users, and others who access or use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p>
          Resume Roast provides AI-powered resume analysis, suggestions, and improvement tools designed to help job seekers enhance their resumes. The Service is provided "as is" and is intended for informational and educational purposes only.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. Use of Service</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">You agree to use the Service only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. You are responsible for all activity that occurs under your account.</p>
        
        <p class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">Prohibited Activities:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Scraping and Automation:</strong> You may not use any robot, spider, scraper, or other automated means to access the Service for any purpose without our express written permission.</li>
          <li><strong>Reverse Engineering:</strong> You may not attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any aspect of the Service, including our AI models and algorithms.</li>
          <li><strong>Abuse:</strong> You may not interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of the Service, including spamming, hacking, or overwhelming our infrastructure.</li>
          <li><strong>Malicious Content:</strong> You may not upload or transmit any content that contains viruses, malware, or any other harmful code.</li>
          <li><strong>Illegal Use:</strong> You may not use the Service for any illegal or unauthorized purpose, or to solicit the performance of any illegal activity.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. User Accounts</h2>
        <p>
          To access certain features of the Service, you may be required to register for an account. You agree to provide accurate, current, and complete information during the registration process and to update such information to keep it accurate, current, and complete.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          You are responsible for safeguarding your password and for all activities that occur under your account. You agree to notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. User Content</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          "User Content" refers to any text, files, resumes, or other materials that you upload, submit, or transmit to the Service.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> You retain full ownership of your User Content. We do not claim any ownership rights over your resumes or personal data.</li>
          <li><strong>License to Process:</strong> By uploading User Content, you grant Resume Roast a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, reproduce, process, and display your User Content solely for the purpose of providing the Service to you (e.g., analyzing your resume).</li>
          <li><strong>Responsibility:</strong> You are solely responsible for your User Content and the consequences of posting or publishing it. You represent that you own or have the necessary rights to your User Content.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The Service and its original content (excluding User Content), features, and functionality are and will remain the exclusive property of Resume Roast and its licensors. The Service is protected by copyright, trademark, and other laws of both Mexico and foreign countries. Our trademarks and trade dress may not be used in connection with any product or service without the prior written consent of Resume Roast.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. AI Disclaimer</h2>
        <div class="p-4 bg-orange-500/10 border border-orange-500/20 rounded-lg">
          <p class="mb-2">
            <strong>Artificial Intelligence:</strong> The suggestions, scores, and feedback provided by Resume Roast are generated by artificial intelligence. While we strive for accuracy, AI systems can make mistakes.
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>The advice provided is for informational purposes only and does not constitute professional career, legal, or hiring advice.</li>
            <li>We do not guarantee that following our suggestions will result in job interviews or offers.</li>
            <li>You should review all AI-generated content for accuracy and appropriateness before using it in your job applications.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Payments and Billing</h2>
        <p class="mb-2">
          Certain aspects of the Service may be provided for a fee or other charge. If you elect to use paid aspects of the Service, you agree to the pricing and payment terms as we may update them from time to time.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Payment Processing:</strong> We use third-party payment processors (e.g., Stripe) to bill you. The processing of payments will be subject to the terms, conditions, and privacy policies of the Payment Processor in addition to these Terms.</li>
          <li><strong>Subscriptions:</strong> If you purchase a subscription, it will automatically renew unless cancelled. You may cancel your subscription at any time through your account settings.</li>
          <li><strong>Refunds:</strong> Refunds are handled on a case-by-case basis and are generally not provided for partial subscription periods, except as required by applicable law.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">9. Service Availability</h2>
        <p>
          We strive to keep the Service up and running; however, all online services suffer occasional disruptions and outages. We are not liable for any disruption or loss you may suffer as a result. We may update, modify, or discontinue any part of the Service at any time, with or without notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">10. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We may terminate or suspend your account and bar access to the Service immediately, without prior notice or liability, under our sole discretion, for any reason whatsoever and without limitation, including but not limited to a breach of the Terms.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Upon termination, your right to use the Service will immediately cease. If you wish to terminate your account, you may simply discontinue using the Service or delete your account through the settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="uppercase text-sm font-bold text-gray-400 mb-2">Please read this section carefully.</p>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, the Service is provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE," without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied.
        </p>
